  "text": "We have presented simple linear models for QTL detection and localization including populational linkage disequilibrium and within-family cosegregation. The methods uses all available information (i.e., multiple markers and pedigrees). The performance of these methods is satisfactory, as shown by simulations. These methods are computationally much simpler than other proposals. Extensions to multiple QTL mapping and genomic selection are straightforward. These methods should help researchers in QTL mapping and marker assisted selection, in particular in livestock species, where the required information is available, just like regression is more used than full-likelihood methods [CITATION_1] , when possible.",
